WEBVTT

00:07.500 --> 00:08.902
Harper?
What are you doing?

00:08.969 --> 00:10.744
Why do you have your
own Career Day booth?

00:11.178 --> 00:14.253
Everyone's always telling me to be
myself, so that's what I'm doing.

00:14.288 --> 00:17.658
Are you interested in a
fascinating career in being me?

00:19.761 --> 00:21.398
I'll be you
if you be me.

00:22.502 --> 00:23.502
Never mind.

00:27.009 --> 00:29.111
Alex! Have you seen
the Action News booth?

00:29.413 --> 00:32.182
I've got to find it before someone
signs Baxter Knight as their mentor.

00:32.217 --> 00:33.986
Baxter Knight,
the weatherman?

00:34.020 --> 00:35.990
That's who you're
choosing as a mentor?

00:36.024 --> 00:37.492
He's not a weatherman.

00:37.526 --> 00:41.230
He's like a weather hero.

00:41.265 --> 00:44.101
His earmuff alerts have
saved me from many an earache.

00:44.135 --> 00:47.107
Luckily, those earmuffs have
saved you from hearing people say

00:47.141 --> 00:49.610
what a doofus you
look like with them on.

00:49.645 --> 00:52.181
I wish I was wearing
them right now.

00:55.820 --> 00:57.289
Oh! There's Baxter.

00:57.323 --> 00:58.958
So, my little friend,

00:58.992 --> 01:01.261
being a weatherman
is the only career here

01:01.295 --> 01:03.297
where you get
to be on TV.

01:03.331 --> 01:06.968
Does that sound like
something you'd like to do?

01:09.739 --> 01:11.006
Mr. Knight.

01:11.040 --> 01:13.441
I'm Justin Russo.
I'm a huge fan.

01:13.475 --> 01:16.544
I've been following you ever
since you introduced Mr. Nimbus,

01:16.578 --> 01:17.878
your cloud hand.

01:18.046 --> 01:20.915
Put on your galoshes.
It's gonna be a wet one.

01:20.949 --> 01:22.616
With the rain.

01:22.650 --> 01:27.020
You remember Mr. Nimbus.
Kid, you want a mentor?

01:27.054 --> 01:31.026
Do I have Mr. Nimbus pajamas
made out of cloud curtains?

01:32.462 --> 01:35.631
I do.

01:36.333 --> 01:37.934
Oh my gosh!

01:38.135 --> 01:41.072
There's one of the many singing
policemen who does a lot of singing

01:41.106 --> 01:42.507
at ball games and stuff.

01:45.378 --> 01:47.179
Leaving, Miss Russo?

01:47.214 --> 01:51.283
And which career counselor
have you roped in?

01:52.619 --> 01:56.455
Well, Mr. Laritate,
you know what I wish?

01:56.490 --> 01:59.625
I wish you were available
to be a mentor,

01:59.659 --> 02:02.995
because you have all the qualities
I'm looking for in a mentor.

02:03.029 --> 02:05.831
You're a "men"

02:05.865 --> 02:09.366
which is in
the word "mentor."

02:10.737 --> 02:14.107
And...

02:14.141 --> 02:15.576
...bolo tie.

02:19.948 --> 02:23.552
Nice tap dancing,
Bojangles.

02:23.586 --> 02:25.287
Tell you what I'm gonna do.

02:25.322 --> 02:26.722
I'll take you up
on that offer.

02:27.157 --> 02:29.292
Let's mosey on down to
the principal's office.

02:29.326 --> 02:31.027
Deputy.

02:31.062 --> 02:33.797
Well, suppose I was gonna end
up there at some point anyway.

